  <entry>
    <title>读书-摘录重拾</title>
    <link href="/2024/07/14/%E8%AF%BB%E4%B9%A6-%E6%91%98%E5%BD%95%E9%87%8D%E6%8B%BE/"/>
    <url>/2024/07/14/%E8%AF%BB%E4%B9%A6-%E6%91%98%E5%BD%95%E9%87%8D%E6%8B%BE/</url>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="蛤蟆先生去看心理医生"><a href="#蛤蟆先生去看心理医生" class="headerlink" title="蛤蟆先生去看心理医生"></a>蛤蟆先生去看心理医生</h1><p>三种人格境界(用词未必专业)</p><ol><li>儿童境界<ol><li>仍然按照童年时期的行为反应进行为人处世</li><li>高兴，愤怒，厌烦等</li></ol></li><li>父母境界<ol><li>喜欢将自己的想法施加于别人</li><li>掌管欲</li></ol></li><li>成人境界<ol><li>儿童境界和父母境界的有机结合</li></ol></li></ol><p class="note note-success">儿童境界过分沉浸于**过去**，成人境界过分关注的是**别人**。</p><p class="note note-success">想要在心态上成为一个成年人，就要关注自己，关注当下。</p><hr><h1 id="华氏451"><a href="#华氏451" class="headerlink" title="华氏451"></a>华氏451</h1><p class="note note-success">城市，是战争的起点，也是战争的终点</p><p class="note note-success">我们外表是流浪汉，内心是图书馆...我们在记忆</p><p class="note note-success">火焰的美丽之处，在于它能摧毁责任和后果</p><p><img src="/2024/07/14/%E8%AF%BB%E4%B9%A6-%E6%91%98%E5%BD%95%E9%87%8D%E6%8B%BE/OIP-C-1.jpg" alt="华氏451是书的熔点"></p><hr><h1 id="人类简史"><a href="#人类简史" class="headerlink" title="人类简史"></a>人类简史</h1><ul><li>story理论：人类是会讲故事的动物  <ul><li>幻想影响着行为</li></ul></li></ul><p class="note note-success">我们生活在由和我们非常不同的人在我们出生很久之前发明的思想牢狱中</p><ul><li>认知革命 <ul><li>从利用自然力量到控制自然力量 </li><li>混种繁衍理论（政治不正确，种族主义）  </li><li>替代理论  </li><li>语言体系决定思维  </li><li>第四权力（记者，嚼舌根的）</li></ul></li></ul><hr><h1 id="演讲与沟通"><a href="#演讲与沟通" class="headerlink" title="演讲与沟通"></a>演讲与沟通</h1><p>下面的摘录来自《演讲与沟通》（第9版）书籍封面的名言水印。</p><p class="note note-success">Ask not what your country can do for you,ask what you can do for your country.——1961肯尼迪就职演讲</p><p>*ps.川普今日遇刺未遂。</p><p class="note note-success">The luckiest man on the face of the earth.——扬基的骄傲</p><p class="note note-success">Slip the surely bonds of the earth.——《高高飞翔》二战飞行员的诗作</p><p class="note note-success">Women's rights are human rights.——希拉里</p><p class="note note-success">I have a dream today. ——马丁路德金</p><p class="note note-success">An iron curtain has been descended across the continent.——丘吉尔，铁幕演说</p><p class="note note-success">The only thing we have to fear is fear itself.——罗斯福就职演说</p><p class="note note-success">Give me liberty or give me death.——帕特里克亨利，美国革命之舌</p><p class="note note-success">Ain't I a woman?——索杰纳·特鲁斯，废奴和女权主义的思想的杰出卫士</p><p class="note note-success">Four score and seven years ago...——林肯在葛底斯堡的演说的开头</p><p class="note note-success">Blood,toil, tears,and sweat.——丘吉尔就职演说</p><hr><h1 id="沙丘"><a href="#沙丘" class="headerlink" title="沙丘"></a>沙丘</h1><p>姐妹会的恐惧格言：</p><p class="note note-success">“I must not fear. Fear is the mind-killer. Fear is the little-death that brings total obliteration. I will face my fear. I will permit it to pass over me and through me. And when it has gone past I will turn the inner eye to see its path. Where the fear has gone there will be nothing. Only I will remain.”</p> ]]></content>
    
    
    
